$ find-installed-perl-modules.pl

`find-installed-perl-modules.pl` is a quick and dirty script to find the location (path) of installed → development/languages/Perl/modules[Perl modules] on a computer.

gh|PerlModules|/_scripts_/find-installed-perl-modules.pl||

sa:
  → development/languages/Perl/modules/_scripts_/whichpm[`whichpm`] is a cross-platform script that locates installed Perl modules by their package name.

  → development/languages/Perl/perldoc#perldoc-l[`perldoc -l Module::Name`]
